The paper focuses on the security performance study of wireless communications, which suggests that it is likely to belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT), Cryptography and Security (cs.CR), and Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of cooperative jamming and opportunistic relaying, which are related to Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) and Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-categories.
